<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-03-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="70" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Señor
                                    <persName type="to">Morla Vicuña</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-03-17"><hi rend="italic">March 17,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 13th instant in regard to the exchange of
                            ratifications of the claims convention signed at Washington on May 24,
                            1897, between the United States and Chile, and to confirm in writing the
                            verbal understanding agreed upon by you and Dr. Hill. The exchange
                            should be postponed until October 15 next.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>